com.interpss.core.net.childnet

Interface ChildNetwork<TBus extends Bus,TBranch extends Branch>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    com.hazelcast.nio.serialization.DataSerializable, org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject, NameTag, org.eclipse.emf.common.notify.Notifier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ChildNetworkImpl

    public interface ChildNetwork<TBus extends Bus,TBranch extends Branch>
extends NameTag
    A representation of the model object 'Child Network'. It has a reference to a (child) network, a parant network, and a set of interface branches, defining the parnet-child connection relationship.
    There are two ways to define a parent/child network relationship:
    1) Parent net and child net are two independent networks. A set of interface branches are used to define parent/child net interface relationship. In essence, a bus in the parent net is mapped to a bus in the child net. The parent net bus and the child net bus might have different bus ids.
    2) Starting from one network, parent net and child net(s) are created by network split. the parent/child relationship is defined by a set of interface branches in the original network.

    The following features are supported:

    • Network
    • Parent Network
    • Interface Branches
    See Also:
